[
    {
        "content": "<p>This proof was broken by <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/pull/1395\">batteries#1395</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Batteries</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>Nat.sqrt</code> now uses <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/4575799f8ee8eb27a18c0fa62bfe87e44541c588/src/Init/Data/Nat/Log2.lean#L38-L41\"><code>Nat.log2</code></a>, which uses <code>decreasing_by</code> and therefore does not reduce.</p>\n<p>An improvement to <code>Nat.log2</code> landed in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/10046\">lean4#10046</a>, but that's not yet available on <code>leanprover/lean4:v4.23.0-rc2</code>.</p>\n<p>Is there an easy workaround for proofs like the above? Should I just wait until the Lean version gets bumped?</p>",
        "id": 536976713,
        "sender_full_name": "David Renshaw",
        "timestamp": 1756640242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess <code>norm_num</code> if you have mathlib</p>",
        "id": 536977337,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756641069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Amusingly, <code>group</code> also works.</p>",
        "id": 536977470,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756641248
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if you don't have mathlib you can unfold <code>Nat.sqrt</code> to get <code>Nat.sqrt.iter</code> and use the characterizing lemmas for log2 (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.le_log2#doc\">docs#Nat.le_log2</a>) to show what the log2 is and then maybe <code>rfl</code> will work</p>",
        "id": 536977472,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756641251
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/536977470\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Amusingly, <code>group</code> also works.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why?</p>",
        "id": 536978680,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1756642483
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/536978680\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/536977470\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Amusingly, <code>group</code> also works.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'm guessing it calls <code>norm_num</code></p>",
        "id": 536978704,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756642509
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it calls <code>ring_nf</code> which calls <code>norm_num</code></p>",
        "id": 536978731,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756642545
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b498015292d2010eb7b6caca844fe9e6bd5b36b1/Mathlib/Tactic/Group.lean#L65-L67\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b498015292d2010eb7b6caca844fe9e6bd5b36b1/Mathlib/Tactic/Group.lean#L65-L67</a></p>",
        "id": 536978746,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756642560
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Stepping up one level to what actually broke in my proof:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">decide</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This worked before <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/29142\">mathlib4#29142</a> and does not work now. Is there a workaround?</p>",
        "id": 536978820,
        "sender_full_name": "David Renshaw",
        "timestamp": 1756642653
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hn</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">nomatch</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hn</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 536978982,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756642838
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks. I got it working, but it's not pretty. <a href=\"https://github.com/dwrensha/compfiles/commit/1f13be8b301843fee3231e6077df7f39d48a6ba5\">https://github.com/dwrensha/compfiles/commit/1f13be8b301843fee3231e6077df7f39d48a6ba5</a></p>",
        "id": 536980418,
        "sender_full_name": "David Renshaw",
        "timestamp": 1756644242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>should we have a <code>norm_num</code> extension to reduce <code>IsSquare</code> on <code>Nat</code> and <code>Int</code> and <code>Rat</code></p>",
        "id": 536980488,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1756644324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/536978680\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/536977470\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Amusingly, <code>group</code> also works.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I had no idea, until Aaron mentioned the fact that internally there is a <code>norm_num</code>.  I found out using <code>hint</code>.</p>",
        "id": 536983423,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756647069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Apologies about this, I didn't entirely overlook this issue but managed to forget that log2 has only been fixed in the future...</p>\n<p>Is it less work to undo these changes and redo them in two weeks, or to leave adaptation notes in place where the breakages occur now, removing them in two weeks?</p>",
        "id": 537010446,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1756676525
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should nontrivial <code>Decidable</code> instance be written with a <code>by decide</code> example after them to catch this type of issue in future?</p>",
        "id": 537012436,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1756678944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(where \"trivial\" means <code>inferInstanceAs &lt;| ...</code>)</p>",
        "id": 537012451,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1756678965
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just noting for completeness: the definitional reduction started working again in <code>leanprover/lean4:v4.24.0-rc1</code>, but recently stopped working once more, due to <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/pull/1447\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/pull/1447</a> I guess.</p>\n<p>(I can work around this, and I think that a <code>norm_num</code> extension sounds like a decent longer term solution.)</p>",
        "id": 544313689,
        "sender_full_name": "David Renshaw",
        "timestamp": 1760184088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a <code>norm_num</code> extension for <code>IsSquare</code> somewhere in the code approved for opensourcing. I'll open a PR this weekend. OTOH, I would prefer to have <code>by decide</code> work on <code>IsSquare 3</code>. As for <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/pull/1447\">batteries#1447</a>, we can switch to a fuel-based definition of <code>iter</code>, see <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/28768\">#28768</a> for an example.</p>",
        "id": 544320134,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1760188066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also do this, which is probably more or less what  the <code>norm_num</code> extension does, just by hand:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_eq_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">refine</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨?_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">h₁</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h₂</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_antisymm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">?_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">?_⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rintro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lt_succ_sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rwa</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">le_iff_lt_add_one</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_lt</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rwa</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">le_sqrt</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">isSquare_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">exists_mul_self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eq_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">isSquare_iff</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">isSquare_iff</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">show</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_eq_iff</span><span class=\"o\">]]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IsSquare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">234123412314123</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">isSquare_iff</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">show</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">234123412314123</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">15301091</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_eq_iff</span><span class=\"o\">]]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 544320325,
        "sender_full_name": "Markus Himmel",
        "timestamp": 1760188241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"214703\">Yury G. Kudryashov</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Nat.2Esqrt.20no.20longer.20reduces.20definitionally/near/544320134\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have a <code>norm_num</code> extension for <code>IsSquare</code> somewhere in the code approved for opensourcing. I'll open a PR this weekend. OTOH, I would prefer to have <code>by decide</code> work on <code>IsSquare 3</code>. As for <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/pull/1447\">batteries#1447</a>, we can switch to a fuel-based definition of <code>iter</code>, see <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/28768\">#28768</a> for an example.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I was gonna open a PR now</p>",
